<details>
  <summary>⚡ EC2 Instance Types</summary>

### General Purpose

Balanced compute, memory, and networking.

### Compute Optimized

High compute power for intensive workloads.

### Memory Optimized

Designed for memory-heavy applications.

### Storage Optimized

Optimized for high-speed storage access.

### Accelerated Computing

Uses GPUs/FPGAs for advanced workloads.

</details>

<details>
  <summary>🏷️ EC2 Instance Families</summary>

* C → Compute optimized
* M → General purpose
* R → Memory optimized
* T → Burstable performance
* G/P → GPU instances
* I → High I/O
* D → Dense storage

</details>

<details>
  <summary>💰 EC2 Pricing Models</summary>

### On-Demand

Pay only for usage.

### Reserved Instances

Lower pricing with long-term commitment.

### Spot Instances

Unused AWS capacity at discounted pricing.

</details>

